        <title>TextLayer object</title>
        <paragraph><literal>app.project.item(index).layer(index)</literal></paragraph>
        <paragraph><strong>Description</strong></paragraph>
        <paragraph>The TextLayer object represents a text layer within a composition. Create it using the <reference internal="True" refuri="layercollection#layercollection-addtext"><inline classes="std std-ref">LayerCollection object’s addText method</inline></reference>. It can be accessed in an item’s layer collection either by index number or by a name string.</paragraph>
        <block_quote>
            <paragraph>TextLayer is a subclass of <reference internal="True" refuri="avlayer#avlayer"><inline classes="std std-ref">AVLayer</inline></reference>, which is a subclass of <reference internal="True" refuri="layer#layer"><inline classes="std std-ref">Layer</inline></reference>. All methods and attributes of AVLayer and Layer are available when working with TextLayer.</paragraph>
        </block_quote>
